[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]A collection of quality-of-life tweaks to reduce grind around energy, sanity, gratitude, tools, meditation, and sleep. Everything is off-by-default or independently toggleable, so you can take only what you want.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Half costs[/b] — separate toggles for halving the cost of energy, gratitude, and sanity whenever the game spends them (crafting, praying, reading, etc.). Each toggle is independent; halve one and leave the others alone if you prefer.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Unlimited stats[/b] — optional overrides for unlimited energy, gratitude, sanity, and health. Turning one of these on automatically turns off its "half cost" counterpart (they can't both apply at once).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Tools that last longer[/b] — boosts the durability of every craftable tool so they break less often. Axes, pickaxes, shovels, fishing rods, hammers, swords, ice axes, and torches are all covered.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-equip replacement tool[/b] — when your current tool breaks mid-task, the next one of the same type in your inventory is equipped automatically so you can keep chopping/mining without rummaging in menus.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Speed up meditation[/b] — reduces the real-time wait while meditating at the pulpit. Pair with the auto-wake option so meditation exits the instant your stats are full instead of running to the configured cap.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Speed up sleep[/b] — same idea for sleeping. The cutscene still plays; the wait just finishes faster. The outside world still advances time normally.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Raise the "tired" threshold[/b] — vanilla slaps a sleep-debuff on you after spending about 300 energy in a day. A configurable slider (350–50,000) lets you push that threshold out so long work sessions don't penalise you.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/66]Regeneration Reloaded[/url] — passively restore life and energy over time. Pairs well with the half-cost options.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speed up crafting across the board. Compatible with Exhaust-less's half-energy option, so faster crafts don't cost you more.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue whole batches of crafts instead of one at a time.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multiply drops, craft outputs, faith, and tech points.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

